The paper deals with ontology matching, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that involves knowledge representation and reasoning. The use of Bayesian networks, decision trees, and association rules suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DB). The probabilistic framework used to integrate different strategies also suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
